<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 5:42PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Jefferson, southeastern Cotton and northeastern Clay Counties through
615 PM CDT...
At 542 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waurika, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waurika, Ryan, Petrolia, Byers and Sugden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
